#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.150"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.150:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.150:0.2"
msgid "15. Diṭṭhivagga"
msgstr "15. Views"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 150. Ajjhattasutta → ajjhattikaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.150:0.3"
msgid "150. Ajjhattasutta"
msgstr "150. In Oneself"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.181"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.150:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

# See BB’s notes here and at SN 22.83 on the dual meaning of upadaya. In addition to the reasons he gives, I think it’s useful to use “grasping” in these contexts, as it helps illuminate the sense of upadanakkhandha.
msgctxt "sn22.150:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ "
"sukhadukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what, do pleasure and "
"pain arise in oneself?”"

# missing quotes in MS
msgctxt "sn22.150:1.3"
msgid "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …"
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.4"
msgid ""
"“rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati rūpaṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“When form exists, because of grasping form, pleasure and pain arise in "
"oneself."

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.5"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … pe …"
msgstr "When feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.6"
msgid "saññāya sati …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.7"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.8"
msgid "viññāṇe sati viññāṇaṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness, pleasure and pain "
"arise in oneself."

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.10"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.11"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.12"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.13"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.14"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya "
"ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.16"
msgid "“Vedanā … pe …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.17"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.18"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.19"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.20"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.21"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.22"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.23"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya "
"ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.24"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.25"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.150:1.26"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.150:1.27"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
